Spermogonia and aecia on 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDCFFCAFB1CFEC3BA9ECE4E" box="[1213,1451,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Grossulariaceae" genus="Ribes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mandshuricum">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDCFFCAFB1CFEC3BA9ECE4E" box="[1213,1451,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">Ribes mandshuricum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDCFFCAFF31FEBFBE73CE6B" box="[144,326,338,365]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Grossulariaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Grossulariaceae</taxonomicName>
) (C). Telia on 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDCFFCAFE48FEBEBDAECE6A" box="[489,667,338,365]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dispalata">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDCFFCAFE48FEBEBDAECE6A" box="[489,667,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">Carex dispalata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(D); 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDCFFCAFD79FEBEBCB2CE6A" box="[728,903,338,365]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latisquarnea">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDCFFCAFD79FEBEBCB2CE6A" box="[728,903,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">C. latisquarnea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C370650EFFDCFFCAFF1CFE9BBDA6CDD2" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD53685FFDCFFCAFF1CFE9BBDA6CDD2" blockId="15.[136,1452,158,724]" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDCFFCAFF1CFE9BBFCACE96" bold="true" box="[189,255,374,400]" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">Note:</emphasis>
—Species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDCFFCAFE35FE9BBEE7CE96" box="[404,466,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Grossulariaceae" genus="Ribes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDCFFCAFE35FE9BBEE7CE96" box="[404,466,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">Ribes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been reported as the spermogonial and aecial host plant of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDCFFCAFB00FE9ABA2CCE96" box="[1185,1305,375,400]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caricina">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDCFFCAFB00FE9ABA2CCE96" box="[1185,1305,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">P. caricina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDCFFCAFA9CFE9ABA91CE96" box="[1341,1444,375,400]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caricis">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDCFFCAFA9CFE9ABA91CE96" box="[1341,1444,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">P. caricis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but species delimitation and host plant range of these species are different according to available references (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDCFFCAFAFEFE77BFF6CEDE" author="Arthur, J. C." pageId="15" pageNumber="236" refId="ref18916" refString="Arthur, J. C. (1934) Manual of the rusts in United States and Canada. Purdue Research Foundation, USA." type="book" year="1934">Arthur 1934</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDCFFCAFF6CFE52BE1BCEDF" author="Ito, S." box="[205,302,446,473]" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" refId="ref19696" refString="Ito, S. (1950) Mycological flora of Japan, vol. 2, no. 3. Yokendo, Tokyo, Japan." type="book" year="1950">Ito 1950</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDCFFCAFE99FE53BED3CEDF" author="Gaumann, E." box="[312,486,446,473]" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" refId="ref19274" refString="Gaumann, E. (1959) Die Rostpilze Mitteleuropas. Buchdruckerei Bucheler Co, Bern, Germany." type="book" year="1959">Gäumann 1959</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDCFFCAFE51FE53BC29CEDE" author="Wilson, M. &amp; Henderson, D. M." box="[496,796,446,472]" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" refId="ref21861" refString="Wilson, M. &amp; Henderson, D. M. (1966) The British rust fungi. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, UK." type="book" year="1966">Wilson &amp; Henderson 1966</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDCFFCAFC86FE53BB27CEDE" author="Hiratsuka, N. &amp; Sato, S. &amp; Katsuya, K. &amp; Kakishima, M. &amp; Hiratsuka, Y. &amp; Kaneko, S. &amp; Ono, Y. &amp; Sato, T. &amp; Harada, Y. &amp; Hiratsuka, T. &amp; Nakayama, K." box="[807,1042,446,473]" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" refId="ref19488" refString="Hiratsuka, N., Sato, S., Katsuya, K., Kakishima, M., Hiratsuka, Y., Kaneko, S., Ono, Y., Sato, T., Harada, Y., Hiratsuka, T. &amp; Nakayama, K. (1992) The rust flora of Japan. Tsukuba-shuppankai, Tsukuba, Japan." type="book" year="1992">
Hiratsuka 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDCFFCAFC3BFE52BCFFCEDE" box="[922,970,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">et al</emphasis>
. 1992
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDCFFCAFBBDFE53BBC4CEDE" author="Zhuang, J. Y. &amp; Wei, S. X. &amp; Wang, Y. C." box="[1052,1265,446,473]" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" refId="ref22054" refString="Zhuang, J. Y., Wei, S. X. &amp; Wang, Y. C. (1998) Flora fungorum Sinicorum, vol. 10, Uredinales (1). Science Press, Beijing, China." type="book" year="1998">
Zhuang 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDCFFCAFBD9FE52BB9CCEDE" box="[1144,1193,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">et al</emphasis>
. 1998
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDCFFCAFB58FE53BA92CEDF" author="Azbukina, Z. M." box="[1273,1447,446,473]" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" refId="ref18941" refString="Azbukina, Z. M. (2005) Rust fungi, Cryptogamic plants, fungi and mosses of the Russian Far East, vol. 5. Dalnauka, Vladivostok, Russia." type="book" year="2005">Azbukina 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDCFFCAFF29FE0FBFF6CEFB" author="Azbukina, Z. M." box="[136,195,482,509]" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" refId="ref18975" refString="Azbukina, Z. M. (2015) Definitorium fungorum Rossiae, Ordo Pucciniales 1. Dal'nauka, Vladivostok, Russia." type="book" year="2015">2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDCFFCAFF70FE0FBD0DCEFA" author="Termorshuizen, A. J. &amp; Swertz, C. A." box="[209,568,482,508]" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" refId="ref21591" refString="Termorshuizen, A. J. &amp; Swertz, C. A. (2011) Dutch rust fungi. Aad Termorsguizen, Netherland." type="book" year="2011">Termorshuizen &amp; Swertz 2011</bibRefCitation>
). Their morphology and host plants are quite variable and therefore, should be taxonomically reconsidered. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDCFFCAFE55FDEABC33CD26" box="[500,774,518,544]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caricis-ribcola">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDCFFCAFE55FDEABC33CD26" box="[500,774,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">Puccinia caricis-ribcola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is described as an independent species to avoid taxonomic confusion from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDCFFCAFEE2FDC6BE8ACD42" box="[323,447,555,580]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caricina">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDCFFCAFEE2FDC6BE8ACD42" box="[323,447,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">P. caricina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDCFFCAFE4DFDC6BD62CD42" box="[492,599,555,580]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caricis">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDCFFCAFE4DFDC6BD62CD42" box="[492,599,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">P. caricis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDCFFCAFDC8FDC6BCEBCD42" authority="Kleb." authorityName="Kleb." box="[617,990,554,580]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="pringhsheimiana">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDCFFCAFDC8FDC6BCA3CD42" box="[617,918,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">Puccinia pringhsheimiana</emphasis>
Kleb.
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDCFFCAFBADFDC6BBBCCD42" box="[1036,1161,555,580]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caricina">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDCFFCAFBADFDC6BBBCCD42" box="[1036,1161,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">P. caricina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) has been reported from northern Asia as a species having spermogonia and aecia on 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDCFFCAFC99FDA3BC43CD6E" box="[824,886,590,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Grossulariaceae" genus="Ribes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDCFFCAFC99FDA3BC43CD6E" box="[824,886,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">Ribes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDCFFCAFC27FDA3BCDFCD6F" author="Ito, S." box="[902,1002,590,617]" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" refId="ref19696" refString="Ito, S. (1950) Mycological flora of Japan, vol. 2, no. 3. Yokendo, Tokyo, Japan." type="book" year="1950">Ito 1950</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDCFFCAFC57FDA3BB92CD6F" author="Gaumann, E." box="[1014,1191,590,617]" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" refId="ref19274" refString="Gaumann, E. (1959) Die Rostpilze Mitteleuropas. Buchdruckerei Bucheler Co, Bern, Germany." type="book" year="1959">Gäumann 1959</bibRefCitation>
), but its teliospore size is longer than that of this species. Teliospores of this species are also morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDCFFCAFB6FFD9EBA9ECD8A" authority="Miura" authorityName="Miura" box="[1230,1451,626,652]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="15" pageNumber="236" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="yokotensis">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDCFFCAFB6FFD9EBA6ACD8A" box="[1230,1375,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">P. yokotensis</emphasis>
Miura
</taxonomicName>
reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7615FFDCFFCAFE8DFD7ABE59CDB7" box="[300,364,663,689]" name="Japan" pageId="15" pageNumber="236">Japan</collectingCountry>
and Russian Far East (
